msIdentifier.repository: Quaker and Special Collections, Rendel Harris

msContents.summary: Two works on grammar copied together in the same hand. The first is a metrical grammar and the second a grammatical homily in four chapters: 1. Nouns, 2. Verbs, 3. Particles, 4. Syntax.

respStmt.persName: ʻAbd al-Karīm Ibn Naʻmū Ibn al-Nās, active 1810
عبد الكريم ابن نعمو ابن الناس،

msItem.colophon: Colophons in Arabic, Arabic Garshuni, and Syriac.

supportDesc.extent: 95 leaves : 210 x 150 (170 x 120) mm bound to 215 x 157
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil added, upper left recto.

layoutDesc.layout: 18 lines in one column along inside margin with another column of notes bordered in red.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in Syriac and Arabic Garshuni; Serto.

decoDesc.decoNote: Comments border ruled in red; rubrications in red; two small illustrations (f. 10v, 86v).

binding.p: Red leather over pasteboard with simple blind-tooled frame of double lines with three lines intersecting in the middle; blind-stamped central mandorla and eight pendants, two on each of the vertical and horizontal axes.

origin.p: Copied completed in Mosul, Iraq by ʻAbd al-Karīm Ibn Naʻmū Ibn al-Nās in 1811 (f. 86v, 95r).
